observations.recommendation:
We recommend that the Local Chief Executive direct:

The Municipal Accountant to report accurately the account balances and actual status/condition should always be considered in reporting;

The Municipal Treasurer being the LO, to verify the Report of Collections and Deposits; check the statement of accountable forms as to initial balances on hand, receipt, issued, and ending balances on hand; make a physical count of the accountable forms remaining in the custody of the collector/teller and check the same against the new balances on hand column. Also, require her to verify the ORs by affixing a signature at the back of the triplicate copy of the last official receipt issued.  She shall count the money turned over to her and sign the certification and receipt portion of all copies of RCD;

Also, the Municipal Treasurer to maintain subsidiary records for each deputized collector supported with files of the RCDs submitted to facilitate easy retrieval of records for validation and verification purposes; and

The Municipal Treasurer or Property Custodian of the AFs to prepare the Statement of Accountability of Accountable Forms with or without monetary value on a monthly basis, duly supported with the requisitioned issue slip by each accountable officer and a copy of the RCD to give an idea as to the serial numbers and the quantity reported on hand.

We recommend that the Local Chief Executive direct the:

SB members and concerned offices to formulate well-defined policy guidelines on the grant of assistance to come up with a resolution in consonance with the guidelines issued by the DSWD;

MSWDO to maintain objectivity, in determining the type, kind, and amount of financial assistance to be recommended for approval of the appropriate authority;

Municipal Accountant to ascertain the completeness of the required supporting documents based on the guidelines; and

MSWDO to prepare and submit MATRIX for the AICS program based on DSWD guidelines as an aid to the SB in the promulgation of well-defined and specific guidelines that would be consistently applied in the grant of financial assistance.

We recommend the following courses of action:

The Municipal Engineering Office:
Provide the Municipal Accountant and the General Services Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road component for road projects; as well as the report on the repair/maintenance of each local road network;

The General Services Officer/Inventory Committee:
Prepare and submit the Report on the Physical Count of the Local Road Network (RPCLRN);
Maintain the Local Road Network Property Cards for each road and road components;

The Municipal Accountant
Maintain subsidiary records for road and road components for every road network.

We recommended the following courses of action:
The Municipal Engineering Office:
 Provide the cost segregation of road description and cost component for every road projects; as well as report on the repair/maintenance of each local road network;
The General Services Officer/Inventory Committee:
 Prepare and submit the Report on the Physical Count of the Local Road Network (RPCLRN);
 Maintain the Local Road Network Property Cards for each roads and road components;
The Municipal Accountant:
 Adhere to the accounting policy on non-inclusion of residual value in the computation of the depreciation expense for the depreciable component of the Local Road Network;
 Prepare the adjusting entry to correct the understatement of Depreciation Expense to correct the error committed;
 Maintain subsidiary records for road and road components for every road network.

To correct the deficiencies, we recommended that the Municipal Mayor and the HRMO:
1. To determine properly the necessity, assess the duties and functions, taking into account their expertise, experience and capacity to handle the position in order to come up with the ideal number of personnel to be hired;
2. To provide in the contract of service the specific details or information such as expected service to be rendered, funding charges, daily rate and to have it signed by the JO employee as acknowledgement to the agreement;
3. Require each JO worker to prepare the accomplishment report duly verified and accepted by the immediate supervisor;
4. Observe proper documentation, sound management and fiscal administration in order to attain efficiency in the use of government funds.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive to:
1. Instruct the HRMO to follow rules and regulation in the grant of monetization of leave credits;
2. Instruct the Municipal Accountant to verify and process claims for payment of monetization supported with complete documentation;
3. Require the employees concerned to submit the required justification of the claims. Failure would result to suspension in audit of the transaction;
4. Require the persons liable to refund the amount in excess of the allowed claim. This recommendation is without prejudice to the issuance of Notice of Suspension/Disallowance.
